<p>In order for the continuous trim to be enabled, <code class="highlighter-rouge">discard</code> option has to be put in for those partitions in <code class="highlighter-rouge">/etc/fstab</code> for which you want to enable the command. If you‚Äôre working with encrypted , you need to consider <code class="highlighter-rouge">/etc/crypttab</code> as well and put in the <code class="highlighter-rouge">discard</code> option there as well.
I‚Äôll do the change now, reboot and simulate this scenario again.</p>

<p>When I delete the file and read from the address with <code class="highlighter-rouge">dd</code> command, I get a different output this time:</p>
